summary: Here’s Disney Channel’s schedule for next week, November 12-18. Next week, reruns of Good Luck Charlie, K.C. Undercover and Liv...
caption:
Here’s Disney Channel’s schedule for next week, November 12-18. Next week, reruns of Good Luck Charlie, K.C. Undercover and Liv and Maddie return to the nighttime schedule. There’s more movies airing during the week, and a slew of Mickey Mouse shorts in-between shows on Sunday, November 18 celebrating Mickey’s 90th Birthday. Sunday 11/18 is also the network premiere of Lego Star Wars: All Stars, and if you’re tired of Bunk’d airing a lot, well it only airs 17 times this week, significantly less compared to the recent months. 

There’s also New Episodes of Andi Mack, Coop & Cami Ask the World, DuckTales, Mickey and the Roadster Racers, Mickey Mouse, PJ Masks, Puppy Dog Pals, Raven’s Home, and Star Wars Resistance.

I literally shouted this at my screen the first time I watched it
summary: Just a reminder that T.J.’s very first interaction with Cyrus was: T.J. Actively aiding Cyrus to accomplish a task that his own...
body:
Just a reminder that T.J.’s very first interaction with Cyrus was: T.J. Actively aiding Cyrus to accomplish a task that his own best friend deemed him incapable of doing. To placate Buffy’s tutoring bargain T.J. was only required to quickly walk up and do this simple task for Cyrus so he could move on with his life. Instead he scoffed, wasn’t having any of this “he can’t”/”I can’t” nonsense and dedicated extra time to instill this boy he just met with some self-confidence and actively encouraged him to accomplish this task on his own. Stepping in to help briefly? Yes. But ultimately letting Cyrus do. it. himself.

Buffy: “He can’t do that”

T.J.: “Hey, Don’t tell him what he can’t do”

Me:
